This paper focuses on developing a method for enabling a robot to learn to predict the effects of its actions and improve its performance without human supervision. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) as the paper deals with planning robot motion. The method involves using deep action-conditioned video prediction models, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The paper also mentions the use of reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with control systems (cs.SY) as it uses model-predictive control to plan robot motion.
